## 6. Pricing Sensitivity Analysis

### Market Pricing Benchmarks

| Tool Category | Price Range | Examples |
|---------------|-------------|----------|
| Prospect Research (Entry) | $3,745–$5,500/yr | iWave Starter, DonorSearch, WealthEngine |
| Prospect Research (Pro) | $10K–$25K/yr | iWave Professional, Windfall |
| Engagement/Communications | $15K–$40K/yr | Gravyty, EverTrue |
| Analytics Platform | $20K–$60K/yr | Custom BI, Kindsight Enterprise |
| CRM (Full Platform) | $50K–$200K+/yr | Blackbaud CRM, Salesforce NPSP |

### Approval Thresholds

| Price Point | Approval Required | Process |
|-------------|-------------------|---------|
| <$15K | Director-level | Minimal procurement; quick decision |
| $15K–$50K | AVP/Director Advancement Services | May require competitive quotes |
| $50K–$100K | VP Advancement | Formal RFP likely; IT security review |
| >$100K | President/CFO | Formal procurement; extended timeline |

### Pricing Model Preferences (Ranked)

1. **Flat annual fee** (most preferred): Predictable budgeting, no usage anxiety
2. **Per-user tiered:** Acceptable if reasonable tiers (5, 10, 25 users)
3. **Usage-based:** Least preferred, creates budget uncertainty

---

## 7. Strategic Go-to-Market Recommendations

### Targeting

1. Target **Director/AVP of Advancement Services** as primary buyer
2. Build champion relationship with **Director of Prospect Research**
3. Focus on institutions with $100M–$1B endowments (sweet spot for budget and pain)
4. Prioritize **Blackbaud CRM users** (larger installed base, more integration pain)

### Positioning

1. Lead with **"complement not compete"** messaging to reduce CRM replacement fear
2. Emphasize **time savings** (40%+ of team time on manual reporting)
3. Position as **"intelligence layer"** that sits on top of existing systems
4. Focus on **actionable insights**, not dashboards or data visualization

### Sales Process

1. Offer **60–90 day pilots** to reduce perceived risk
2. Provide **security documentation proactively** (SOC 2, FERPA, encryption)
3. Build **case studies with quantified ROI** from mid-tier institutions
4. Develop **reference network** of similar-sized institutions willing to take calls

### Pricing Strategy

1. Price initial offering in **$20K–$40K range** to fit within Director-level approval threshold
2. Use **flat annual pricing** (most preferred by buyers)
3. Offer **pilot-to-paid conversion** path with discounted first year
4. Create **ROI calculator** showing staff time savings to justify investment

### Channel Strategy

1. **CASE District Conferences** (Feb–Mar): Volume lead generation, demos
2. **Apra International** (August): Champion-building, technical credibility
3. **Regional Apra chapters** (year-round): Grassroots relationship building
4. **LinkedIn:** Target advancement professionals in "Advancement Services" roles

---

## 8. Competitive Landscape Summary

### Key Competitors by Category

| Category | Players | Positioning |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| AI-Powered Engagement | Gravyty, EverTrue+DonorSearch | Email/communication automation |
| Predictive Analytics | Kindsight (Reeher), Windfall | Wealth screening, propensity modeling |
| Prospect Research | iWave, DonorSearch, WealthEngine | Data enrichment, capacity ratings |
| CRM Platforms | Blackbaud, Salesforce NPSP | Core donor management |

### Market Whitespace

**"Intelligence Layer for Advancement"** — CRM-agnostic analytics platform that:
- Integrates with any CRM (Blackbaud, Salesforce, Slate)
- Provides actionable insights (not just dashboards)
- Reduces manual research and reporting time
- Identifies high-potential prospects automatically
- Tracks engagement signals across channels

